Linked Lists

@ Benefits
i. Easily inserted/removed without reallocation/reorganization
- Items need not be stored contiguously in memory
ii. Allow insertion & removal of nodes at any point

@ Types
i. Singly Linked List
data field + next field
ii. Doubly Linked List
data field + next field + prev field
iii. Circular Linked List
- Tail linked back to head
- Ability to traverse full list beginning at any given node

@ Application
i. Stack
ii. Queue
iii. Maintain references to active processes, threads & other dynamic objects
iv. Hash table
v. Binary tree
